# Wanix wasi-sdk (C fixtures)

Applies when editing Wanix WASI `.c` sources, `build-wasm-c.sh`, install docs, or `tasks/groups/wanix.ts` wasm build tasks. See [`ops/fixtures/wanix/README.md`](../../ops/fixtures/wanix/README.md), skill `wanix-zed-cafe-export`.

## Policy

| Topic | Rule |
|-------|------|
| C fixtures | **Require** wasi-sdk — `hello.c`, `zedcaferead.c`, `zedcafewrite.c`, `zedcafelist.c` |
| WAT fixtures | **Only** `hold.wat`, `termbridge.wat` via `wanix:wasm:build` (wabt) |
| Install path | Canonical **`/opt/wasi-sdk`**; override via `$WASI_SDK_PATH` only |
| Setup | `sh ops/fixtures/wanix/install-wasi-sdk.sh` — no Homebrew `wasi-sdk` formula |
| `wanix:wasm:build:c` | **Must exit 1** when SDK missing or `clang` broken |
| `wanix:wasm:build:all` | C step is required — composite fails without SDK |

## Build tasks

| Task | Needs wasi-sdk |
|------|----------------|
| `wanix:wasm:build` | No (WAT only: hold, termbridge) |
| `wanix:wasm:build:c` | **Yes** — all `*.c` |
| `wanix:wasm:build:all` | **Yes** (C step) |

## Prohibited

- `exit 0` skip when wasi-sdk absent in [`build-wasm-c.sh`](../../ops/fixtures/wanix/build-wasm-c.sh)
- Re-adding `.wat` for C-covered fixtures (`hello`, `zedcaferead`, `zedcafewrite`) as a no-SDK fallback
- `~/.local/wasi-sdk` or other shadow install paths in build scripts
- `rm -rf` in install scripts — abort if target exists; user relocates manually
- Patching wasi-sdk tarball / libedit in repo to paper over a bad install

## Allowed

- WAT-only fixtures via [`build-wasm.sh`](../../ops/fixtures/wanix/build-wasm.sh)
- Pointing users to `install-wasi-sdk.sh` + README

Cross-link: rule `fixtures.mdc`, rule `wanix-term-bridge.mdc`.
